---
title: Salmon En Papillote with Couscous Pilaf, Asparagus, and Tarragon Chive Sauce
description: It doesn’t matter if you can pronounce en papillote; the appeal of this classic French technique is easy to understand. When you wrap salmon fillets in foil, then cook them in the oven (or on the grill), they basically roast in their own juices, locking in flavor and moisture throughout. In this recipe, they’re finished with a drizzle of herb sauce and served next to asparagus and couscous. Basically, it’s an equation for timeless, classic deliciousness.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/salmon-en-papillote-353dd4db.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/salmon-en-papillote-45276cc1.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/salmon-en-papillote-591e127b2310a87a76080c92
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 44 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 90 mg
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}. Zest @lemon{1} until you have ½ tsp zest, then halve crosswise. Slice one half into thin rounds. Trim and discard bottom inch from @asparagus{8%oz} stalks. Mince @chives{1/4%oz}. Mince @tarragon{1/4%oz} until you have 1 TBSP.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add @yellow onion{1}(finely chopped) and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @water{1%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{a large pinch}, then bring to a boil. Once boiling, add @couscous{1/2%cup}. Cover, remove from heat, and let stand until rest of meal is ready.

Tear off two sheets of @aluminum foil{a few sheets}, each large enough to wrap a salmon fillet. Lay @skin-on salmon{12%oz} fillet on each. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place two @lemon{1}(sliced into thin rounds) on top of each, then sprinkle with a small amount of @chives{} (save some chives for the sauce). Fold over aluminum foil and crimp edges to seal into two packets.

> Be careful when unwrapping the cooked salmon—it may release steam.

Place packets with salmon on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Toss asparagus with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} on other side of sheet. Roast in oven until salmon is cooked through and asparagus is tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tarragon, remaining chives, half the zest, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{}(for sauce). Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a squeeze or two of @lemon{} (to taste).

Fluff couscous with a #fork{} and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a pinch of remaining zest. Divide between plates along with salmon and asparagus. Drizzle with sauce and a squeeze of lemon.

> For a pretty presentation, leave the lemon rounds on the salmon—just remove them before eating.